The '''Émile Picard Medal''' (or Médaille Émile Picard) is a medal named for [[Émile Picard]] awarded every 6 years to an outstanding mathematician<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/37513025|title=Recognizing excellence in the mathematical sciences : an international compilation of awards, prizes, and recipients|date=1997|publisher=JAI Press|others=Jaguszewski, Janice M.|isbn=0762302356|location=Greenwich, Conn.|oclc=37513025}}</ref> by the [[Institut de France]], [[Académie des sciences]].
